@startuml
' ============================================================================
' sluice - Proxy (CTX-001) / CAP-005 Runtime lifecycle
' Panic recovery state for a single request goroutine.
' Derived from real code: internal/middleware/recover.go (Recoverer, SafeGo).
' ============================================================================
title "CAP-005: panic recovery on the request goroutine"

[*] --> Serving : Recoverer (OUTERMOST) wraps next.ServeHTTP

state Serving {
  Serving --> Completed : handler returns normally
}

Serving --> Recovering : panic raised downstream

state Recovering {
  Recovering --> Reraised : rv == http.ErrAbortHandler
  Recovering --> Logged   : any other panic value
}

Reraised --> [*] : panic(rv) — net/http handles abort\n(no 500 written, connection aborted)

Logged --> Wrote500 : logging.LogPanic (ERROR + stack)\nthen WriteHeader(500) best-effort
Wrote500 --> [*] : process SURVIVES; net/http keeps serving

Completed --> [*]

note right of Logged
A panic in a DETACHED goroutine cannot be caught here
(recover only works on the same stack). Such goroutines
MUST be launched via SafeGo, which installs its own recover.
end note
@enduml
